+### Summary
+The requested BUG-SM-015 fix set is not present in the current file. The reopened-table flow still lacks session-aware grouping, session-aware consumers, and the `openSessions`/orphan-invalidation ground truth needed to separate old and new table sessions.
+
+### Findings
+1. [P1] Fix B.1 is not implemented — `orderGroups` still groups hall orders by plain `tableId` only in `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:3737-3786`. The block still builds `tableGroups[tableId]`, never stores `sessionId`, `openSessionId`, or `compositeKey`, and therefore still merges closed-session orders with a reopened table's new session into one card. FIX: replace the whole `orderGroups` memo with the session-aware `tableId__sessionId` implementation from Fix B.1 and carry `sessionId`, `openSessionId`, and `compositeKey` on every table group.
+2. [P1] Fixes B.2-B.6 are also missing, so the UI still uses table-level identity everywhere — `filteredGroups` and `tabCounts` in `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:3829-3868` do not compare `group.sessionId` against the current open session, `handleBannerNavigate` at `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:4102-4116` still accepts a raw `groupId`, the live card DOM keeps `data-group-id={group.id}` at `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:2283`, and the rendered cards still use `key={group.id}`, `expandedGroupId === group.id`, `handleToggleExpand(group.id)`, and `highlightGroupId === group.id` at `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:4415-4421`. FIX: apply Fix B.2 through Fix B.6 so tab assignment uses `group.sessionId` and React/DOM state uses `group.compositeKey`.
+3. [P1] Fix A and Fix C are absent, so there is no session ground truth to support the reopened-table split — the current file contains zero hits for `openSessions`, `openSessionByTableId`, `staleTime: 5_000`, `maybeTableIdOrCompositeKey`, or `orphanInvalidateSigRef`, and it jumps from the requests error handling block straight into `lastUpdatedAt` around `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:3527`. FIX: restore the `openSessions` `useQuery`, rebuild `openSessionByTableId`, set its `staleTime` to `5_000`, and add the orphan-detection `useEffect` after that memo exactly as specified in Fix A and Fix C.
