+# Codex Writer Findings — Unknown
+Chain: ks-som-b2-1-v7-260417-260417-154836-f018
+
+## Findings
+1. [P1] Fix B.1 is not implemented — `orderGroups` still groups hall orders by plain `tableId` only in `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:3737-3786`. The block still builds `tableGroups[tableId]`, never stores `sessionId`, `openSessionId`, or `compositeKey`, and therefore still merges closed-session orders with a reopened table's new session into one card. That reproduces BUG-SM-015's core failure: the reopened table inherits the historical card state instead of appearing as a fresh active card. FIX: replace the whole `orderGroups` memo with the session-aware `tableId__sessionId` implementation from Fix B.1 and carry `sessionId`, `openSessionId`, and `compositeKey` on every table group.
+2. [P1] Fixes B.2-B.6 are also missing, so the UI still uses table-level identity everywhere — `filteredGroups` and `tabCounts` in `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:3829-3868` do not compare `group.sessionId` against the current open session, `handleBannerNavigate` at `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:4102-4116` still accepts a raw `groupId`, the live card DOM keeps `data-group-id={group.id}` at `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:2283`, and the rendered cards still use `key={group.id}`, `expandedGroupId === group.id`, `handleToggleExpand(group.id)`, and `highlightGroupId === group.id` at `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:4415-4421`. Even if grouping were split later, these consumers would still collapse reopened sessions back onto one table-level card identity, breaking tab placement, expand/highlight state, and banner navigation. FIX: apply Fix B.2 through Fix B.6 exactly so active/completed assignment uses `group.sessionId`, while React/DOM state uses `group.compositeKey` and favorites/upstream callbacks stay on `group.id`.
+3. [P1] Fix A and Fix C are absent, so there is no session ground truth to support the reopened-table split — the current file contains zero hits for `openSessions`, `openSessionByTableId`, `staleTime: 5_000`, `maybeTableIdOrCompositeKey`, or `orphanInvalidateSigRef`, and it jumps from the requests error handling block straight into `lastUpdatedAt` around `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:3527`. Without the `openSessions` query, the 5-second staleness window, and the orphan-triggered invalidation effect, the page has no current TableSession source to learn that a table was reopened, so Fix B cannot reliably move the old session to Completed and show the new one in Active promptly. FIX: restore the `openSessions` `useQuery`, rebuild `openSessionByTableId`, set its `staleTime` to `5_000`, and add the orphan-detection `useEffect` after that memo exactly as specified in Fix A and Fix C.
+
